<div class="indented"><a id="comment-2078284"></a>


<div  id="comment-2078284" class="comment comment-published clear-block">
      <div class='column-top'><div class='column-wrapper'>
  
      <div class='comment-submitted clear-block'> <div class='byline'>Posted by <span class='username'>Mairead</span></div><div class='date'>Mar 14 2012 - 5:27pm</div></div>
  
      </div></div>
  
      <div class='column-main'><div class='column-wrapper'>
  


      <div class='comment-content clear-block prose'>
      <p>You misunderstand my position.  </p>
<p>There are too many humans, but that doesn't make any current humans surplus (as far as I'm concerned, the psychopaths are surplus, but I don't count them as human).</p>
<p>The way to solve the problem is not by killing people now alive, but rather to implement a mandatory limit, enforced by post-partum sterilisation, of 0.5 live birth per person with no exceptions.  </p>
<p>Enforcing that for the rest of this century, while implementing crash programs for re-forestation, rebuilding public infrastructure, and supporting populations elsewhere in the world would painlessly drop the human population back to the size it was in the 17th century, and at the same time solve --or put on the road to solution-- most of the problems our overpopulation has created:  oceans would de-acidify and fish species recover, mammalian species now near extinction would begin recovery as we withdrew from their habitats, CO2 and methane would drop, climate would re-stabilise, and we would become smarter because of the increased oxygen in the air from the forests.</p>
<p>Our problems look intractable, but only a few factors --three, to be exact-- maintain them.  Change those three factors, and our problems would begin to vanish like bad dreams.</p>
<p>One of those factors is human overpopulation.</p>
<p>The second factor is feudalism:  the belief that A should be allowed to lay claim to the land and tools on which B's life depends.</p>
<p>The third factor is Platonic "guardian" philosophy:  the belief that A knows how to run B's life better than B does, and therefore should have power over B.</p>
    </div>
