<div class="indented"><a id="comment-2078774"></a>


<div  id="comment-2078774" class="comment comment-published clear-block">
      <div class='column-top'><div class='column-wrapper'>
  
      <div class='comment-submitted clear-block'> <div class='byline'>Posted by <span class='username'>Mairead</span></div><div class='date'>Mar 15 2012 - 8:14am</div></div>
  
      </div></div>
  
      <div class='column-main'><div class='column-wrapper'>
  


      <div class='comment-content clear-block prose'>
      <p>Gee, not only aren't you an anarchist, you don't even know what the word means!</p>
<p>An anarchist is someone who believes there should be no separate ruling class, not that there should be no state.  "Arch" has always meant ruler, never state.</p>
<p>Human beings live in community.  It's what keeps us from having to sleep in trees at night.  Those like you, who don't like community because you imagine that it restricts your freedom, are immature at best --about at the level of a 14yo boy.  Your fantasies, which you've exposed here, are of unlimited power with no responsibility:  Master of the Universe.  </p>
<p>Anarchists don't think that way.  We're probably the most responsible people in the world because of how aware we are that, without community, we're back sleeping in that tree at night, prey to the first big cat who wants a snack.  </p>
<p>People without community have no real freedom because any mistake, any accident can be their last.  So their energy, instead of being available to them for elective activities, goes into protective ones instead.  That's not freedom, that's slavery.  Futile, too, because it's simply not possible for an individual to guard against all mistakes, all accidents, all natural calamities, all creatures of superior force.</p>
<p>Real freedom consists in knowing that other people will share with us every day, and care for us if something happens.  When we know that our food is covered every day even if we haven't joined the foraging, and that a dozen people will leap to our defence if that cat comes after us, and that if we get sick someone will be there to wipe our face and bring us water, and that all that's expected of us is that we willingly do our share of the foraging, cat-repulsion, and face-wiping, we're free in the most complete possible sense of the term.</p>
    </div>
      <div class='comment-links clear-block'><ul class="links"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"><span><a href="/user/login?destination=node%2F80387%23comment-form">Login</a> or <a href="/user/register?destination=node%2F80387%23comment-form">register</a> to post comments</span></li>
