      <div class='column-main'><div class='column-wrapper'>
  


      <div class='comment-content clear-block prose'>
      <p>I agree. It you are going to hunt, you need to kill quickly. Nothing more sickening than wounding an animal. This device would be a great aid for Hunter's Safety, I know it would have been great when I took the class. </p>
<p>We have problems here in California too, we don't have many of the top level predators and there is very little hunting here in this area (although the rest of the state is much better for animal management) and the deer are eating everything and being hit by cars daily. The wild pigs are getting into people's yards. </p>
<p>Part of conservation is a rational animal management program and this seems like a good tool to train that.</p>
