<div  id="comment-2078000" class="comment comment-published clear-block">
      <div class='column-top'><div class='column-wrapper'>
  
      <div class='comment-submitted clear-block'> <div class='byline'>Posted by <span class='username'>TapMeYouFascists</span></div><div class='date'>Mar 14 2012 - 1:24pm</div></div>
  
      </div></div>
  
      <div class='column-main'><div class='column-wrapper'>
  


      <div class='comment-content clear-block prose'>
      <p>Not everyone wants to sustain their bodies with estrogen mimicking soybean protein. Some of us can still feel the pointy teeth in our mouths and don't want to support CAFOs. And yes, humans have taken pretty much all the land previously utilized by Nature to support healthy ecosystems with multiple checks on population levels. As long as civilization continues this occupation of the landbase, it is up to game management to maintain animal populations at some semblance of carrying capacity, or risk destroying what little remains of viable ecology before humans go the way of the dodo. As an organic permaculture farmer who slaughters his own animals as humanely as possible I can tell you this: Death is always painful, often necessary and it is almost never instantaneous. But it is the responsibility of those to whom the task falls to make it as swift, ethical and efficient as possible. This tool furthers those ends, and is therefore a GOOD THING!</p>
    </div>
